gomodel:SYNGO_3866  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Fig.3: \"Presynaptic LPA signaling induces excitatory STD\"\n\nFig.4: \"LPA modulates AMPAR-mediated neurotransmission via LPA1/Gαi/o-PLC\"\n\nFig.5: \"LPA rearranges SVs at excitatory boutons in a MLCK-dependent manner.\"\n\n9/7/2018 Pim:\nThe authors show that LPA modulates the presynaptic RRP of glutamatergic SVs, that LPA1 is located in the presynaptic compartment, and that KD of LPA1 to a large extent supresses the LPA effect on glutamatergic SVs.. Experimental description: - \"Multiple immunolabeling confocal images of the HN from P7 rats showing a close relationship between LPA1-ir patches and structures expressing the nonphosphorylated form of neurofilament H\"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0593-3443" ;
        dc:date           "2018-07-09" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_3866" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

